WEBVTT

00:02.502 --> 00:04.254
<i>- ♪ Crashing through</i>
<i>the crowded halls ♪</i>

00:04.337 --> 00:05.255
<i>♪ Dodging girls</i>
<i>like Ping-Pong balls ♪</i>

00:05.338 --> 00:07.590
<i>♪ Just to reach the bathroom</i>
<i>on time ♪</i>

00:07.674 --> 00:09.259
<i>♪ Leaping over laundry piles ♪</i>

00:09.342 --> 00:11.094
<i>♪ Diapers you can smell</i>
<i>for miles ♪</i>

00:11.177 --> 00:13.555
<i>♪ Guy's got to do</i>
<i>what he can to survive ♪</i>

00:13.638 --> 00:14.848
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>

00:14.931 --> 00:16.599
<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>

00:16.683 --> 00:18.059
<i>- ♪ Duck, dodge, push,</i>
<i>and shove ♪</i>

00:18.143 --> 00:19.936
<i>♪ Is how we show our love ♪</i>

00:20.019 --> 00:21.438
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house,</i>
<i>in the Loud house ♪</i>

00:21.521 --> 00:23.106
<i>- ♪ One boy and ten girls ♪</i>

00:23.189 --> 00:24.441
<i>♪ Wouldn't trade it</i>
<i>for the world ♪</i>

00:24.524 --> 00:27.652
<i>- ♪ Loud Loud Loud ♪</i>

00:27.736 --> 00:28.945
{\an8}<i>♪ Loud house ♪</i>

00:29.028 --> 00:30.155
{\an7}- Poo-poo.

00:32.031 --> 00:34.993
<i>[instrumental music]</i>

00:35.076 --> 00:39.289
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:42.208 --> 00:43.418
[blow dryer whirring]

00:43.501 --> 00:45.295
- Dinner's almost ready, guys!

00:45.378 --> 00:47.547
- Uh, Leni, what are you doing?

00:47.630 --> 00:49.632
- Defrosting the goulash
Dad left us.

00:49.716 --> 00:51.760
{\an1}- Maybe you should
try the stove.

00:51.843 --> 00:52.927
- Good idea.

00:53.011 --> 00:54.179
I was worried this would give

00:54.262 --> 00:55.847
the goulash split ends, anyway.

00:55.930 --> 00:57.390
- Forget the goulash!

00:57.474 --> 00:58.516
My favorite racecar driver,
Bobbie Fletcher,

00:58.600 --> 01:01.686
is holding a contest tonight
at the Burpin' Burger!

01:01.770 --> 01:04.147
<i>Whoever finds the burger</i>
<i>with the tire-marked wrapper</i>

01:04.230 --> 01:06.941
<i>gets to be an honorary member</i>
<i>of her pit crew.</i>

01:07.025 --> 01:08.860
- I see you got
the winning wrapper.

01:08.943 --> 01:11.446
Welcome aboard, Lana.

01:11.529 --> 01:12.405
- I know what you're gonna say.

01:12.489 --> 01:14.657
Mom and Dad left us plenty
of food to eat

01:14.741 --> 01:16.201
while they're away
for the weekend, but--

01:16.284 --> 01:18.661
[car honking]

01:18.745 --> 01:20.663
- You had us
at "Burpin' Burger"!

01:20.747 --> 01:21.998
<i>[low jazz music]</i>

01:22.081 --> 01:23.625
- Hops! Jacket jump!

01:23.708 --> 01:27.128
[frog croaking]

01:27.212 --> 01:28.671
Whoo-hoo! Yeah!

01:28.755 --> 01:30.965
- Siblings, I'd like
to call your attention

01:31.049 --> 01:34.552
to the rapidly descending ice
crystals, street name, snow.

01:34.636 --> 01:37.680
- Fine, Lis, you can stay here
and eat the goulash.

01:37.764 --> 01:40.391
- I call shotgun!

01:40.475 --> 01:41.893
[tires screeching]

01:42.769 --> 01:44.896
<i>- Please welcome</i>
<i>racing champion...</i>

01:44.979 --> 01:47.106
[engine revving]
<i>Bobbie Fletcher!</i>

01:47.190 --> 01:50.360
[cheering]

01:50.443 --> 01:52.070
- Yes!
- There she is!

01:52.153 --> 01:53.863
- Thanks for coming out,
racing fans!

01:53.947 --> 01:56.199
I want to give a huge thanks
to my sponsor, Burpin' Burger.

01:56.282 --> 01:59.035
Let me tell ya, you can't get
past the starting line

01:59.118 --> 02:01.538
without quality fuel,
and mine is right here,

02:01.621 --> 02:04.332
the Big Belcher
with extra pickles.

02:04.415 --> 02:07.085
[cheering]

02:07.168 --> 02:09.795
I can't wait to have one
of you folks on my pit crew.

02:09.878 --> 02:11.798
All you gotta do is
find the burger wrapper

02:11.881 --> 02:13.758
that looks just like this.

02:13.842 --> 02:15.635
Ladies and gentlemen,

02:15.718 --> 02:16.719
start your stomachs.
[horn blares]

02:16.803 --> 02:20.557
[cheering]

02:20.640 --> 02:22.517
- Give me a dozen burgers,

02:22.600 --> 02:23.810
and try to make one
of them the winner.

02:23.893 --> 02:27.856
- A dozen? Wow, you must really
want to be on that pit crew.

02:27.939 --> 02:31.067
- Oh, yeah, Bippity Fletchman,
huge fan.

02:31.150 --> 02:33.236
- Actually, her name is--
- Don't care!

02:33.319 --> 02:35.113
Just gonna sell
the winning wrapper

02:35.196 --> 02:38.199
to some sucker for big bucks.

02:38.283 --> 02:39.659
Come to Flippy.

02:39.742 --> 02:40.743
- No wrapper, no wrapper,
no wrapper.

02:40.827 --> 02:42.829
{\an1}- Dang it.

02:42.912 --> 02:44.539
All losers.

02:44.622 --> 02:46.749
{\an3}Keep those burgers cooking,
Slim, 'cause I'll be back

02:46.833 --> 02:49.544
{\an3}for more once I scratch
up some moolah.

02:49.627 --> 02:53.631
- We'd like ten Big Belchers
and one Baby Belcher, please.

02:53.715 --> 02:55.925
- Okay, that'll be $25.

02:56.009 --> 02:58.553
- Uh, don't worry, guys.
I got this.

02:58.636 --> 02:59.762
Let's see...

02:59.846 --> 03:01.681
my gum collection, banana peel,

03:01.764 --> 03:04.100
owl's foot, ah, here it is.

03:04.183 --> 03:07.186
- Oh, one of our
"Kids Eat Free" coupons. Great.

03:07.270 --> 03:09.272
Wait, did you just
say owl's foot?

03:09.355 --> 03:12.525
- Yeah, isn't she a hoot?
[laughs]

03:12.609 --> 03:14.027
{\an1}- Next.

03:14.110 --> 03:16.654
- All right, guys, dig in.

03:23.036 --> 03:25.079
{\an1}- Sorry we didn't find
the winning wrapper, Lana.

03:25.163 --> 03:26.623
[frog croaks]

03:26.706 --> 03:29.292
- The frozen precipitation
is accumulating rapidly.

03:29.375 --> 03:31.294
I suggest we skedaddle.

03:31.377 --> 03:33.796
- Wait, don't you guys
want another round?

03:33.880 --> 03:35.632
- We can have seconds?

03:35.715 --> 03:37.800
- How are we gonna pay for it?

03:38.509 --> 03:40.803
<i>[mischievous music]</i>

03:40.887 --> 03:42.680
- Hops, sticky snag.

03:42.764 --> 03:44.265
[frog croaks]

03:44.349 --> 03:46.351
Bullseye.

03:46.434 --> 03:48.353
{\an3}I'll take 11 more burgers,
please,

03:48.436 --> 03:49.187
and I have another coupon.

03:49.270 --> 03:52.523
- [groans] Why is it so sticky?

03:54.525 --> 03:55.652
{\an3}- [burps]

03:55.735 --> 03:57.153
- [groans] Still nothing.

03:57.236 --> 03:59.072
We have to order more burgers.

03:59.155 --> 04:02.659
- Ah, in light of the worsening
meteorological conditions--

04:02.742 --> 04:04.160
[burps]

04:04.243 --> 04:05.995
Perhaps we should
follow the lead

04:06.079 --> 04:08.456
of the other patrons
and am-scray.

04:08.539 --> 04:09.832
- Come on, hurry, hurry.

04:09.916 --> 04:11.793
- I do not like the look
of that sky.

04:11.876 --> 04:13.252
- Oh, let them leave.

04:13.336 --> 04:15.004
That'll make our chances
even better.

04:15.088 --> 04:16.964
Come on, you guys,
one more round.

04:17.048 --> 04:18.382
[all groaning]

04:18.466 --> 04:20.301
- I can't eat anything else.

04:20.385 --> 04:23.846
- I can't even joke
about burgers right now.

04:23.930 --> 04:25.473
- You don't have to eat 'em.

04:25.556 --> 04:26.808
Hops and I will take them home
for breakfast.

04:26.891 --> 04:28.726
- [burps]

04:28.810 --> 04:30.269
[all sighing]

04:30.353 --> 04:31.896
- Great, be right back.

04:31.980 --> 04:34.107
Don't move.

04:34.190 --> 04:37.694
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:37.777 --> 04:39.195
[frog croaks]

04:40.446 --> 04:42.115
- [gasps]
[thud]

04:42.198 --> 04:44.200
- Let's try that again, buddy.

04:44.283 --> 04:45.743
- Hey, you little sneak.

04:45.827 --> 04:48.121
You want more burgers,
you got to pay for them.

04:48.204 --> 04:50.873
- Okay, um, not a prob.

04:50.957 --> 04:53.835
<i>[playful guitar music]</i>

04:53.918 --> 04:59.799
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:59.882 --> 05:02.051
[inhales deeply]

05:03.177 --> 05:05.263
11 more burgers, please.

05:05.346 --> 05:07.223
{\an1}- Jeez...

05:07.306 --> 05:08.891
- Whoops, that's
my chicken beak.

05:08.975 --> 05:11.060
{\an1}- [groans]

05:11.144 --> 05:12.603
Are you guys almost done?

05:12.687 --> 05:14.856
{\an1}I want to get out of here.
I rode my bike to work.

05:14.939 --> 05:16.566
- Don't worry.
We'll be leaving soon.

05:16.649 --> 05:19.110
I got a great feeling
about this batch.

05:20.945 --> 05:23.072
- Sorry, Lana.
I don't have it.

05:23.156 --> 05:24.449
- Me neither, dude.

05:24.532 --> 05:26.075
{\an1}- Same here, I guess
that's a wrap.

05:26.159 --> 05:29.078
[laughs] Oh, sorry.

05:29.162 --> 05:32.915
- [breathes deeply]

05:32.999 --> 05:34.125
Dang it.

05:34.208 --> 05:35.418
I guess I'm not gonna be

05:35.501 --> 05:37.253
on Bobbie Fletcher's pit crew.

05:37.336 --> 05:41.340
- Ew. Someone wrapped my burger
in this dirty old rag.

05:41.424 --> 05:43.259
- Leni! You found it!

05:43.342 --> 05:44.927
{\an3}You found it!
[laughs]

05:45.011 --> 05:47.013
{\an1}- Finally.

05:47.096 --> 05:50.975
- [laughs] Finding this wrapper
means the world to me.

05:51.059 --> 05:52.769
Thanks for all your help, guys.

05:52.852 --> 05:53.603
- All right, now let's get home

05:53.686 --> 05:55.688
so I can let 'em rip
in privacy.

05:55.772 --> 05:56.898
- [groans]

05:56.981 --> 05:58.191
Can I bunk with you guys
tonight?

06:00.359 --> 06:02.028
[all gasping]
- Oops.

06:02.111 --> 06:03.780
This must be the closet where
they keep their snow.

06:03.863 --> 06:05.156
- No, Leni.

06:05.239 --> 06:06.783
We're snowed in.

06:06.866 --> 06:09.952
- Aw man, are we gonna be stuck
here all night?

06:10.036 --> 06:12.246
{\an1}- No, I just worked
a 12-hour shift.

06:12.330 --> 06:15.083
{\an1}I can't take another second
in this greasy dungeon.

06:15.166 --> 06:16.876
[grunts]

06:17.877 --> 06:21.422
- Sorry, buddy, there's snow
way out. [giggle]

06:21.506 --> 06:22.840
{\an1}- [cries]

06:22.924 --> 06:23.549
[engine revving]

06:23.633 --> 06:25.760
[tires screeching]
[thud]

06:25.843 --> 06:27.470
- Guess who just earned a bunch

06:27.553 --> 06:30.473
{\an3}of cheddar digging stranded
suckers out of the snow?

06:30.556 --> 06:33.309
Lay a dozen burgers on me,
bicycle boy.

06:33.392 --> 06:34.936
- You can save your cheddar.

06:35.019 --> 06:36.979
I already found
the winning wrapper.

06:37.063 --> 06:38.648
- What? Bull hockey.

06:38.731 --> 06:41.067
That baby was gonna
make me a fortune.

06:41.150 --> 06:42.985
I'm out!
- Flip, wait!

06:43.069 --> 06:45.363
Can you give us a ride home?
We're stuck here.

06:45.446 --> 06:46.906
- Stuck, are ya?

06:46.989 --> 06:49.575
I can help you
out...for a price.

06:49.659 --> 06:51.661
Let's say, ah, I don't know...

06:51.744 --> 06:53.538
one winning wrapper?

06:53.621 --> 06:55.248
- What? No way!

06:55.331 --> 06:57.208
Guys, we worked so hard
for this.

06:57.291 --> 06:59.001
I'll get us home, I promise.

06:59.085 --> 07:01.379
- Suit yourself,
but this offer expires

07:01.462 --> 07:04.006
the second that door
hits my keister.

07:04.090 --> 07:05.675
- Wait, I'll give you anything.

07:05.758 --> 07:07.176
My employee discount.

07:07.260 --> 07:09.387
- Throw in a jumbo sack
of curly fries

07:09.470 --> 07:11.055
and you got a deal.

07:11.139 --> 07:13.474
- I'm free!

07:13.558 --> 07:15.685
- Catch you on the Flip side.

07:15.768 --> 07:17.812
- Well, I hope you know
what you're doing, Lana,

07:17.895 --> 07:20.606
because I am literally not
sleeping on hamburger wrappers.

07:20.690 --> 07:21.858
- No worries.

07:21.941 --> 07:22.817
Flip's truck cleared the path

07:22.900 --> 07:24.944
so we just need to make it
to Vanzilla--

07:25.027 --> 07:26.320
[truck reversing beeps]

07:26.404 --> 07:27.738
<i>- Whoops!</i>

07:27.822 --> 07:29.574
[all groaning]

07:29.657 --> 07:31.200
- Guys, I got this.
Trust me.

07:31.284 --> 07:33.077
I'll get us out.

07:33.161 --> 07:35.121
<i>[low jazz music]</i>

07:35.204 --> 07:37.039
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:37.123 --> 07:39.625
And I know just how to do it.

07:42.295 --> 07:43.546
[sniffs]

07:43.629 --> 07:46.174
Leaking gas
and old string cheese.

07:46.257 --> 07:47.884
We're close to Vanzilla.

07:47.967 --> 07:49.802
Charles has been giving me
bloodhound lessons.

07:52.889 --> 07:54.390
There you are, old girl.

07:54.473 --> 07:57.476
I'll have you out in a jiffy.

07:57.560 --> 07:59.395
Hey guys! We're going home.

07:59.478 --> 08:02.607
- You literally did it, Lans.

08:02.690 --> 08:05.443
- Thanks.
[cheering]

08:05.526 --> 08:09.614
- Hah, and you guys wanted me
to give my wrapper to Flip.

08:09.697 --> 08:13.826
[engine grinding]

08:13.910 --> 08:15.369
Hmm.

08:15.453 --> 08:17.079
Better check out
the engine block...

08:17.163 --> 08:19.415
of ice?

08:19.498 --> 08:20.875
[all groaning]

08:20.958 --> 08:22.418
{\an1}- If you'd just let Flip
give us

08:22.501 --> 08:23.878
a ride we'd be home by now.

08:23.961 --> 08:25.755
- [groans] There's
no signal here.

08:25.838 --> 08:28.633
I'm gonna warm up inside
and use the landline.

08:28.716 --> 08:30.760
- Don't worry, Hops,
we'll figure this out.

08:32.510 --> 08:35.431
I know just the thing.

08:35.514 --> 08:37.642
Burger warming lamp.

08:39.727 --> 08:41.562
all: Dang it.

08:41.645 --> 08:43.981
{\an1}[shivering]
- No signal. No landline.

08:44.065 --> 08:45.191
Bobby has no idea where I am.

08:45.274 --> 08:47.443
I feel so alone.

08:47.526 --> 08:49.570
{\an3}- Bobby is the least
of our problems.

08:49.654 --> 08:52.615
{\an3}I'm so cold I can't feel
my tushie.

08:52.698 --> 08:54.909
- Come on, guys.
We need to stay positive.

08:54.992 --> 08:55.868
We could be here all night.

09:00.915 --> 09:02.583
- Hops, not now.

09:02.667 --> 09:05.127
We'll play later.
Hops.

09:06.712 --> 09:09.298
<i>[somber piano music]</i>

09:09.382 --> 09:11.842
- [coughs]
- Oh, poor thing.

09:11.926 --> 09:13.261
I'll keep you warm.

09:13.344 --> 09:15.346
- I made cute shawls.

09:15.429 --> 09:17.098
Who wants one?

09:17.181 --> 09:19.558
- I'd rather freeze
my tushie off

09:19.642 --> 09:22.311
than be seen wearing napkins.

09:22.395 --> 09:23.771
- If we huddle together

09:23.854 --> 09:25.398
{\an1}and conserve
our dwindling body heat,

09:25.481 --> 09:27.900
{\an1}we may be able to stave
off hypothermia.

09:27.984 --> 09:30.152
I forgot how much
I hate huddling.

09:30.236 --> 09:33.698
- Aw man, I've been so selfish.

09:35.741 --> 09:37.243
[rumbling]

09:38.202 --> 09:39.829
[all screaming]

09:39.912 --> 09:41.664
- [sputtering]

09:41.747 --> 09:44.292
- Flip? What are
you doing here?

09:44.375 --> 09:45.960
- I tracked him down.

09:46.043 --> 09:48.838
I just followed the smell
of curly fries and B.O.

09:48.921 --> 09:50.673
{\an1}- You went out
in these conditions?

09:50.756 --> 09:52.967
{\an1}You could have lost a digit
to frostbite.

09:53.050 --> 09:54.260
- I had to.

09:54.343 --> 09:55.344
I couldn't let you guys suffer

09:55.428 --> 09:56.554
all night because of me.

09:56.637 --> 09:58.347
So now Flip will take us home.

09:58.431 --> 10:01.851
{\an3}- Right after I get
that wrapper.

10:01.934 --> 10:03.436
{\an1}[all gasp]

10:03.519 --> 10:05.354
{\an1}- We know how much
that wrapper meant to you.

10:05.438 --> 10:08.816
{\an1}Thanks for giving it up
and getting us out of here.

10:08.899 --> 10:10.568
- Thanks, Lans.
- Mighty dece of you.

10:10.651 --> 10:12.486
{\an1}- We know how much
this means to you, Lana.

10:14.530 --> 10:18.367
{\an3}- Well, lookee here,
another sucker.

10:18.451 --> 10:21.329
Sit tight, chief.
I'll be back for you later.

10:21.412 --> 10:22.955
- Wait, that's Bobbie Fletcher.

10:23.039 --> 10:25.166
Stop, Flip!
We have to help her.

10:25.249 --> 10:26.709
{\an3}- [sighs]

10:26.792 --> 10:28.377
[truck reversing beeps]

10:28.461 --> 10:30.212
- Excuse me, Ms. Fletcher?

10:30.296 --> 10:31.380
What happened?

10:31.464 --> 10:32.757
- Engine died.

10:32.840 --> 10:34.383
This baby can hit 210
in the straightaway,

10:34.467 --> 10:38.179
{\an1}but throw a little snow
at her and she conks out.

10:38.262 --> 10:40.806
- Mind if I...?
- It's all yours.

10:40.890 --> 10:42.516
<i>[rock music]</i>

10:42.600 --> 10:44.727
- See if she'll turn over now.

10:44.810 --> 10:46.228
[engine revving]

10:46.312 --> 10:48.731
- Dang. My pit crew isn't even
that fast.

10:48.814 --> 10:50.316
What's your name, sport?

10:50.399 --> 10:51.734
- Lana Loud.

10:51.817 --> 10:53.319
{\an3}- Well, thank you,
Lana Loud.

10:53.402 --> 10:55.071
Give me a call
when you're 18.

10:55.154 --> 10:56.906
I could use someone
like you on my team.

10:56.989 --> 10:59.700
- Wow. Thanks!

10:59.784 --> 11:02.912
[cheering]
- Way to go, Lana.

11:02.995 --> 11:04.997
- Hey, Bippity Fletchman!

11:05.081 --> 11:06.874
She may have fixed your car,

11:06.957 --> 11:08.542
but I'm one
who brought her here.

11:08.626 --> 11:10.002
How about a little something
for me?

11:10.086 --> 11:11.837
- Coming right up, pal.

11:11.921 --> 11:13.381
[engine revving]

11:13.464 --> 11:15.049
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:16.884 --> 11:19.720
<i>[pleasant music]</i>

11:19.804 --> 11:23.849
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:23.933 --> 11:26.602
<i>all: ♪ Dashing</i>
<i>through the snow ♪</i>

11:26.685 --> 11:28.312
<i>♪ In a luxury SUV ♪</i>

11:28.396 --> 11:30.064
<i>♪ We're making up some time ♪</i>

11:30.147 --> 11:31.107
♪ Because we stopped to pee,
hey ♪

11:31.190 --> 11:33.776
[laughter]

11:33.859 --> 11:35.319
- This is great!

11:35.403 --> 11:38.447
My first ever vacation
with Clyde and his dads!

11:38.531 --> 11:41.117
And if it's anything
like their soufflés,

11:41.200 --> 11:43.077
it's going to be awesome!

11:43.160 --> 11:44.995
Whoa! What is that?

11:45.079 --> 11:47.331
<i>- Oh, that's the Ramp</i>
<i>of Insanity.</i>

11:47.415 --> 11:49.166
<i>It's a near-vertical drop</i>

11:49.250 --> 11:51.585
<i>where you can reach speeds</i>
<i>of 100 miles an hour,</i>

11:51.669 --> 11:54.296
<i>then get launched 5,000 feet</i>
<i>in the air.</i>

11:54.380 --> 11:56.298
- Sweet! Do we get to go on it?

11:56.382 --> 11:57.299
{\an1}- [gasps]

11:57.383 --> 12:00.177
{\an3}- And that is why
I'm doing the driving.

12:00.261 --> 12:01.595
{\an3}Lincoln, let me translate
for Howard...

12:01.679 --> 12:04.265
- No.
- Don't worry, buddy.

12:04.348 --> 12:06.767
We have tons
of other fun stuff to do.

12:08.561 --> 12:10.312
- What happened?

12:10.396 --> 12:13.149
- You passed out when we asked
about the Ramp of Insanity.

12:13.232 --> 12:14.817
- The Ramp of Insanity?!

12:14.900 --> 12:16.485
{\an1}[sighs]

12:17.653 --> 12:19.613
<i>[singsongy] Here we are!</i>

12:19.697 --> 12:21.115
- Whoo-hoo!

12:21.198 --> 12:22.825
Race you to the front door.
- Ah, ah, ah.

12:22.908 --> 12:24.076
Hold on.

12:25.536 --> 12:27.455
{\an1}- My dads don't want us
to slip on the ice.

12:27.538 --> 12:28.998
{\an3}- Ah.

12:29.081 --> 12:31.041
Wow. Nice.

12:31.125 --> 12:33.127
{\an3}- Ah, ah, ah.
Hold on.

12:33.210 --> 12:34.503
[machines whirring]

12:34.587 --> 12:35.880
Now we're good.

12:35.963 --> 12:37.840
{\an1}- My dads don't want us
to get splinters.

12:37.923 --> 12:38.340
{\an3}- Ah.

12:38.424 --> 12:41.135
[both cheering]

12:41.218 --> 12:43.220
- So what should we do first?
Go sledding?

12:43.304 --> 12:45.973
- I'll grab Big Red II!
- Ah, ah.

12:47.766 --> 12:50.186
There. Now we're good.

12:50.269 --> 12:52.021
{\an1}- My dads don't want us
to get frostbite.

12:52.104 --> 12:53.314
{\an3}- Ah.

12:57.109 --> 13:00.196
- Here. I've had a lot
of practice with this.

13:00.279 --> 13:01.655
- What if I have to pee?

13:01.739 --> 13:03.157
- Not a problem.

13:03.240 --> 13:04.909
Just give me 15 minutes notice.

13:04.992 --> 13:08.496
- Pilot to copilot,
we are ready for launch.

13:10.789 --> 13:11.874
Both: Ah, ah.

13:11.957 --> 13:13.459
- Good thing we found

13:13.542 --> 13:14.668
that clearance sale
on mattresses.

13:14.752 --> 13:15.711
- And on bubble wrap.

13:15.794 --> 13:16.962
Now we're good.

13:18.130 --> 13:19.590
{\an3}- Okay...

13:19.673 --> 13:21.717
{\an3}Well, this is still
gonna be fun.

13:21.800 --> 13:25.471
{\an3}Here we go!
Whee!

13:26.430 --> 13:28.390
Uh, why aren't we moving?

13:28.474 --> 13:30.017
- Oh, we called ahead and asked

13:30.100 --> 13:31.560
the groundskeeper
to level the hillside.

13:31.644 --> 13:33.479
{\an1}- My dads don't want us
to break our necks.

13:33.562 --> 13:34.688
{\an3}- [sighs]

13:34.772 --> 13:35.898
Watch out, Clyde.

13:35.981 --> 13:37.691
I'm gonna show you no mercy.

13:37.775 --> 13:39.068
- Well I'm gonna show
you even less.

13:39.151 --> 13:42.488
Unless you want me to,
in which case I totally will.

13:42.571 --> 13:43.572
- Okay, whatever.

13:43.656 --> 13:46.075
both: Ready...aim...fire!

13:46.158 --> 13:49.286
both: No!

13:49.370 --> 13:50.538
[thud]

13:50.621 --> 13:52.414
- What are you--what?

13:52.498 --> 13:54.250
- My dads don't want us
to end up in the hospital

13:54.333 --> 13:55.960
because of an ice ball
to the head.

13:56.043 --> 13:57.795
- [grunts]

13:57.878 --> 14:00.005
- Who wants hot chocolate?

14:00.089 --> 14:01.924
- Ooh, I do!
- Me, too, please!

14:02.007 --> 14:04.677
{\an3}- Here you go, boys.
Enjoy.

14:04.760 --> 14:05.844
[both slurping]

14:05.928 --> 14:08.097
- Um, this is kind of cold.

14:08.180 --> 14:09.598
- Yeah, my dads don't want us

14:09.682 --> 14:11.267
{\an1}to scald the roofs
of our mouths.

14:11.350 --> 14:14.270
{\an3}- [groans] Clyde, permission
to speak freely?

14:14.353 --> 14:15.688
- Granted.
- Look.

14:15.771 --> 14:17.106
Your dads are awesome,

14:17.189 --> 14:18.983
{\an3}but this trip has
made me realize

14:19.066 --> 14:21.777
{\an3}that they are really
overprotective.

14:21.860 --> 14:23.153
- Yeah, maybe a little,

14:23.237 --> 14:24.697
{\an1}but they're just looking out
for me.

14:24.780 --> 14:26.699
{\an3}- Clyde, you're wearing
a seat belt

14:26.782 --> 14:28.200
on the couch.

14:28.284 --> 14:29.451
{\an1}- My dads don't want me
to get injured

14:29.535 --> 14:30.786
in an earthquake.

14:30.869 --> 14:31.829
We are only three states away

14:31.912 --> 14:33.247
from a fault line.

14:37.209 --> 14:39.295
Holy shamoly!
You're right, Lincoln.

14:39.378 --> 14:41.880
{\an1}This is...
[grunts] crazy!

14:41.964 --> 14:44.508
I'm gonna talk
to my dads right now.

14:44.592 --> 14:46.302
- Go get 'em, buddy.

14:46.385 --> 14:48.053
[machine whirring]
- Dads, do you have a second?

14:48.137 --> 14:49.888
- Sure, what's up, peanut?

14:49.972 --> 14:50.973
{\an3}- Howard! We agreed
we wouldn't call him that

14:51.056 --> 14:54.143
{\an3}in case he develops
a peanut allergy someday.

14:54.226 --> 14:56.395
- What's up, uh, apple slice?

14:56.478 --> 14:57.813
Was the cocoa too hot?

14:57.896 --> 14:59.440
{\an1}I knew I should have put in
more ice cubes.

14:59.523 --> 15:01.191
- That's exactly
what I want to talk about.

15:01.275 --> 15:04.153
I think--I think you guys are
too overprotective.

15:04.236 --> 15:05.154
[both gasp]

15:05.237 --> 15:06.822
With the couch seat belts

15:06.905 --> 15:08.240
and the tree mattresses
and the bubble wrap...

15:08.324 --> 15:09.408
[both gasp]

15:09.491 --> 15:10.075
I'm not a little kid anymore.

15:10.159 --> 15:12.077
I can take care of myself.

15:12.161 --> 15:13.662
You don't have to worry
about me so much.

15:13.746 --> 15:15.080
- Worry? We don't worry.

15:15.164 --> 15:18.083
- I'm scheduling a group
session with Dr. Lopez.

15:18.167 --> 15:19.627
We have to talk about this.

15:19.710 --> 15:21.795
- No, you don't need
to call Dr. Lopez.

15:21.879 --> 15:23.964
You just need
to let go a little bit.

15:24.048 --> 15:24.840
- What do you think, Howie?

15:24.923 --> 15:28.636
{\an3}- Well, maybe we could try.
[cries]

15:28.719 --> 15:30.054
{\an1}- I agree.

15:30.137 --> 15:32.014
- You guys are the best.
Thank you.

15:32.097 --> 15:33.515
{\an1}- I'm still calling Dr. Lopez.
Just for me.

15:33.599 --> 15:36.185
<i>[adventurous music]</i>

15:36.268 --> 15:38.771
{\an1}- Okay, buddy,
now the fun really begins.

15:38.854 --> 15:41.315
- I'll sled to that.

15:41.398 --> 15:44.193
Yahoo!
- Faster, faster!

15:44.276 --> 15:45.944
[sled beeps]

15:46.028 --> 15:48.030
<i>[music slows down]</i>

15:48.113 --> 15:51.909
- I'm so sorry.
That wasn't supposed to happen.

15:51.992 --> 15:53.535
- Well, that's a relief.

15:53.619 --> 15:55.079
- It was supposed
to be a parachute.

15:55.162 --> 15:57.122
{\an3}- Dads, you said
you were going to let go.

15:57.206 --> 15:59.541
{\an1}- We're sorry, Clyde,
we're just not there yet.

15:59.625 --> 16:02.044
- It's a dangerous world
and we don't think

16:02.127 --> 16:03.796
you're ready to
face it on your own.

16:03.879 --> 16:04.880
- I disagree.

16:04.963 --> 16:05.923
- Why don't we revisit

16:06.006 --> 16:07.216
this in another decade?

16:07.299 --> 16:08.884
- [frustrated growl]

16:08.967 --> 16:11.345
<i>[tense music]</i>

16:12.680 --> 16:14.264
<i>- [screams]</i>

16:14.348 --> 16:15.265
- [yelps]

16:15.349 --> 16:18.185
I should have buckled up.

16:18.268 --> 16:21.188
Whoa! Smooth floors!

16:21.271 --> 16:22.398
{\an1}[thud]
What's going on?

16:22.481 --> 16:25.401
- [stammers]

16:25.484 --> 16:26.902
- Let me translate for Howard.

16:26.985 --> 16:28.278
Clyde's in mortal danger.

16:28.362 --> 16:29.780
- What?

16:29.863 --> 16:31.615
- We found this note
from him when we woke up.

16:31.699 --> 16:35.244
- "Dear Dads, I'm off to sled
the Ramp of Insanity.

16:35.327 --> 16:37.413
I hope this will prove
that I'm capable

16:37.496 --> 16:39.415
of taking care of
myself. Love, Clyde."

16:39.498 --> 16:41.125
Oh, no, what have I done?

16:41.208 --> 16:42.459
- What do you mean?

16:42.543 --> 16:44.211
- Well, after the buffed floors

16:44.294 --> 16:45.921
{\an1}and the couch seat belt
and everything,

16:46.004 --> 16:49.049
{\an1}I kind of told him you guys
were too overprotective.

16:49.133 --> 16:51.677
I'm sorry, I didn't think
he'd take it this far.

16:51.760 --> 16:53.345
- Uh, it's okay, Lincoln.

16:53.429 --> 16:55.639
Just don't tell Howard.
- [groans]

16:55.723 --> 16:57.516
Tell me what?
- Uh, nothing.

16:57.599 --> 17:00.227
[laughs] Let's just focus
on stopping Clyde before he--

17:00.310 --> 17:02.813
- Don't finish that sentence!
[cries]

17:02.896 --> 17:04.772
- Don't worry, Mr. McBrides.

17:04.857 --> 17:06.023
I got this.

17:06.108 --> 17:08.109
[echoing]
Clyde, do you copy?

17:08.193 --> 17:10.779
{\an1}Wait, he's still
in the house somewhere.

17:12.489 --> 17:15.242
Oh, he just left his
walkie-talkie behind.

17:15.325 --> 17:16.743
- [whimpers]

17:16.827 --> 17:18.829
{\an1}- Come on, we're going
to the Ramp of Insanity.

17:18.912 --> 17:21.707
- There he is!
I see him!

17:21.790 --> 17:23.876
{\an1}- Clyde, honey!
Don't do it!

17:23.959 --> 17:25.461
Just climb back down.

17:25.544 --> 17:27.921
{\an3}- Oh, Howie, he must be
paralyzed with fear.

17:28.005 --> 17:29.506
- He gets that from me.

17:29.590 --> 17:31.633
- We'll just have to go up
and get him.

17:31.717 --> 17:33.051
{\an3}- No, no, no.
We'll go, Lincoln.

17:33.135 --> 17:33.635
I don't want you getting hurt.

17:33.719 --> 17:35.971
- No, I have to go.

17:36.054 --> 17:37.598
Clyde is my best friend,

17:37.681 --> 17:39.558
and I'm not just gonna stand
here while he--

17:39.641 --> 17:40.726
{\an1}- Don't finish that sentence.
[cries]

17:40.809 --> 17:43.395
- Okay, we'll all go up

17:43.479 --> 17:45.898
but very carefully.

17:47.232 --> 17:47.733
I hope this thing is safe.

17:47.816 --> 17:50.319
- I'm sure it's fine.

17:50.402 --> 17:53.155
{\an8}There'd be a sign if it wasn't.

17:58.452 --> 18:00.120
We're here, buddy.
You're safe.

18:00.204 --> 18:03.165
Everything's going to be--okay?

18:03.248 --> 18:05.209
- That's just an old sign.

18:05.292 --> 18:06.877
Where's my baby?

18:06.960 --> 18:08.504
[wind blowing]

18:11.590 --> 18:12.674
[both screaming]

18:12.758 --> 18:16.845
My baby could be lying injured
in a ravine somewhere.

18:16.929 --> 18:20.307
{\an1}We need to get off this thing
and find him.

18:20.390 --> 18:22.434
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

18:22.518 --> 18:26.271
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:26.355 --> 18:27.815
all: We're trapped.

18:27.898 --> 18:31.276
[echoes]
trapped....trapped...

18:31.360 --> 18:33.153
- Whew. Cold.

18:33.237 --> 18:35.948
Dads? Lincoln? Hello?

18:38.242 --> 18:39.618
<i>- Lincoln, come in.</i>

18:39.701 --> 18:42.037
<i>This is--</i>
- Clyde! You're okay.

18:42.120 --> 18:42.996
- Where are you, son?
Did you go down the ramp?

18:43.080 --> 18:45.082
{\an1}- Sweetie, did you break
anything?

18:45.165 --> 18:46.375
Can you wiggle your toes?

18:46.458 --> 18:47.960
{\an1}Stay still!
Don't move your head.

18:48.043 --> 18:50.546
- Guys, I'm fine.
I didn't go down the ramp.

18:50.629 --> 18:52.089
<i>- You didn't?</i>
- Oh, heck no.

18:52.172 --> 18:54.550
I got there and realized
you guys were right.

18:54.633 --> 18:55.551
<i>That thing is dangerous.</i>

18:55.634 --> 18:57.928
<i>So I turned around</i>
<i>and went back home.</i>

18:58.011 --> 18:59.346
- Oh, thank goodness.

18:59.429 --> 19:01.348
- That was good judgement, son.

19:01.431 --> 19:03.016
<i>- So, where are you guys?</i>

19:03.100 --> 19:04.935
- Uh, funny story...

19:05.018 --> 19:06.520
- Guys! I'm here.

19:06.603 --> 19:08.730
- Clyde! Did you call
the ranger?

19:08.814 --> 19:10.732
- I did,
but I got his voicemail.

19:10.816 --> 19:13.735
{\an1}- What? Harold,
our next vacation is Chicago,

19:13.819 --> 19:15.237
not the sticks.

19:15.320 --> 19:17.072
- Don't worry.
We don't need the ranger.

19:17.155 --> 19:18.949
Because I'm rescuing you.

19:19.032 --> 19:20.492
- Oh, no, you're not.

19:20.576 --> 19:21.410
Go back and call
the fire department,

19:21.493 --> 19:24.705
or the police department,
or Nana Gayle.

19:24.788 --> 19:25.539
But you are not coming up here.

19:25.622 --> 19:28.083
[screams]

19:28.166 --> 19:28.792
Okay, come up here.

19:28.876 --> 19:31.086
But please be careful.

19:31.169 --> 19:32.254
- I'm gonna say
this

19:32.337 --> 19:34.548
one last time...

19:34.631 --> 19:36.717
Don't worry.

19:36.800 --> 19:39.303
<i>[adventurous music]</i>

19:39.386 --> 19:40.846
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:40.929 --> 19:42.598
- Oh, I can't look.
- Clyde!

19:42.681 --> 19:44.099
{\an3}What about your crippling fear
of heights?

19:44.182 --> 19:47.644
- I was trying not
to think about that.

19:47.728 --> 19:48.645
- Forget I mentioned it.

19:48.729 --> 19:52.941
{\an3}- It's okay.
I'm just trying to concentrate.

19:53.025 --> 19:55.360
- Honey, if you're thinking
of climbing that tree,

19:55.444 --> 19:57.237
don't forget
about your sap allergy.

19:57.321 --> 19:59.948
- I took my pills.
For gosh sakes.

20:00.032 --> 20:02.201
- [gasps] Oh, this is too much.

20:02.284 --> 20:03.493
Now I can't look.

20:03.577 --> 20:04.870
- I still can't.

20:04.953 --> 20:06.455
{\an3}- You guys are rubbing
off on me.

20:06.538 --> 20:09.541
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:12.336 --> 20:14.504
- That was very brave, son.

20:14.588 --> 20:16.465
Even if it took five years
off my life.

20:16.548 --> 20:19.760
- We're not out
of the woods yet.

20:19.843 --> 20:22.262
Let's ramp this up.

20:22.346 --> 20:22.930
Quickly, everybody.
Get on.

20:23.013 --> 20:25.974
There's only one way down.

20:26.058 --> 20:27.851
You're just gonna have
to trust me.

20:27.935 --> 20:29.269
Hurry!

20:29.353 --> 20:33.523
Hold on to your butts.
all: Way ahead of you.

20:33.607 --> 20:36.693
all: [screaming]

20:36.777 --> 20:37.569
- Since this is the end,

20:37.653 --> 20:39.655
there's something I need
to tell you.

20:39.738 --> 20:40.614
I never liked
your beef bourguignon.

20:40.697 --> 20:42.991
- I don't go to the gym
when I say I do.

20:43.075 --> 20:44.368
I go to the donut shop.

20:44.451 --> 20:46.995
[all screaming]

20:47.079 --> 20:48.497
- A parachute.

20:48.580 --> 20:50.624
Ah, good thinking, Clyde.

20:50.707 --> 20:52.042
- I got the idea from you.

20:52.125 --> 20:55.003
- Honey, we owe you an apology.

20:55.087 --> 20:57.381
You obviously can take care
of yourself.

20:57.464 --> 20:58.298
{\an3}- Well, it's all 'cause
of you guys.

20:58.382 --> 21:00.884
{\an3}You taught me
to always be prepared.

21:00.968 --> 21:03.679
{\an1}- From now on, we promise not
to be so overprotective,

21:03.762 --> 21:04.680
and this time, we mean it.

21:04.763 --> 21:08.183
{\an3}- Thanks. I'm lucky
to have Dads like you.

21:08.266 --> 21:10.185
- I'll give them
a little privacy.

21:10.269 --> 21:10.686
all: Get in here, Lincoln.

21:10.769 --> 21:13.146
all: Hugs!

21:13.230 --> 21:14.481
- Come on, let's head back
to the cabin

21:14.564 --> 21:16.191
for some actual hot cocoa.

21:16.274 --> 21:18.360
- Really?
- Well, hot-ish.

21:18.443 --> 21:20.070
So what was
that you were saying

21:20.153 --> 21:21.697
about my beef bourguignon?

21:21.780 --> 21:23.573
- I can't remember
because I'm still wondering

21:23.657 --> 21:26.159
why we bother paying
for a gym membership.

21:26.243 --> 21:27.577
- Touché.

21:27.661 --> 21:29.288
- Okay, Howie, ready to let go?

21:29.371 --> 21:30.831
- [sighs] Ready
as I'll ever be.

21:30.914 --> 21:33.875
- Man, we are
fantastic parents.

21:33.959 --> 21:36.712
- Pilot to co-pilot,
we are ready for launch.

21:36.795 --> 21:38.964
{\an1}Now the fun really, really
begins.

21:39.047 --> 21:39.923
- I'll sled to that.

21:40.007 --> 21:42.509
- All right!
- Yahoo!

21:42.592 --> 21:45.554
[cheering]
- Faster, faster!

21:45.637 --> 21:47.097
[both yelling]

21:47.180 --> 21:48.390
[thud]

21:48.473 --> 21:49.808
[both laughing]

21:49.891 --> 21:51.893
- That was awesome.
- Let's go again!

21:51.977 --> 21:54.271
- [laughs] Looks like
we're getting the hang

21:54.354 --> 21:56.982
of not being
so overprotective, huh, Howie?

21:57.065 --> 21:58.608
Howie?

21:58.692 --> 22:00.235
I'll get the smelling salts.

22:02.904 --> 22:04.322
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Cramped inside</i>
<i>this tiny space ♪</i>

22:04.406 --> 22:05.490
{\an8}<i>♪ May sound bad</i>
<i>but ain't the case ♪</i>

22:05.574 --> 22:07.576
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Loud house ♪</i>

22:07.659 --> 22:11.538
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Duck and dodge</i>
<i>and push and shove ♪</i>

22:11.621 --> 22:15.459
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way we show</i>
<i>our love in the Loud house ♪</i>

22:15.542 --> 22:17.044
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Loud house ♪</i>

22:17.127 --> 22:18.754
{\an8}<i>♪ Laundry piles</i>
<i>stacked up high ♪</i>

22:18.837 --> 22:19.588
{\an8}<i>♪ Hand-me-downs</i>
<i>that make me cry ♪</i>

22:19.671 --> 22:21.631
{\an8}<i>♪ Stand in line</i>
<i>to take a pee ♪</i>

22:21.715 --> 22:22.924
{\an8}<i>♪ Never any privacy ♪</i>

22:23.008 --> 22:24.843
{\an8}<i>♪ Chaos with 11 kids ♪</i>

22:24.926 --> 22:27.012
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way</i>
<i>it always is ♪</i>

22:27.095 --> 22:28.889
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>
